<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <title>DC Platform BSS AWS IAM Role Request</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Calibri, Arial, sans-serif;
      font-size: 11pt;
      color: #1f2933;
    }
    h1 {
      font-size: 18pt;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }
    h2 {
      font-size: 14pt;
      margin-top: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }
    p {
      margin: 6px 0;
    }
    table {
      border-collapse: collapse;
      width: 100%;
      margin-top: 8px;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    th, td {
      border: 1px solid #9aa5b1;
      padding: 6px;
      vertical-align: top;
    }
    th {
      background: #e4e7eb;
      font-weight: bold;
    }
    code {
      font-family: Consolas, monospace;
      font-size: 10pt;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>DC Platform BSS AWS IAM Role Request</h1>

  <p>
    Please create the following IAM roles for the DC Platform BSS EKS prototype.
    These roles are intended to be reused by the smoke test and the real Terraform-based deployment wherever possible.
  </p>

  <h2>IAM Roles</h2>

  <table>
    <tr>
      <th>#</th>
      <th>IAM Role Name</th>
      <th>Purpose</th>
      <th>Create Now?</th>
      <th>Permissions To Attach Now</th>
      <th>Trust Policy Now</th>
      <th>Update Later After EKS/OIDC Exists</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>1</td>
      <td><code>dc-platform-bss-eks-cluster-role</code></td>
      <td>EKS control plane role for smoke test and real EKS cluster.</td>
      <td>Yes</td>
      <td>AWS managed policy: <code>AmazonEKSClusterPolicy</code></td>
      <td>Allow service principal <code>eks.amazonaws.com</code> to run <code>sts:AssumeRole</code>.</td>
      <td>No later update normally needed.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>2</td>
      <td><code>dc-platform-bss-eks-node-role</code></td>
      <td>EKS managed node group role for EC2 worker nodes.</td>
      <td>Yes</td>
      <td>
        AWS managed policies:
        <code>AmazonEKSWorkerNodePolicy</code>,
        <code>AmazonEC2ContainerRegistryPullOnly</code>,
        <code>AmazonEKS_CNI_Policy</code>
      </td>
      <td>Allow service principal <code>ec2.amazonaws.com</code> to run <code>sts:AssumeRole</code>.</td>
      <td>No later update normally needed.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>3</td>
      <td><code>dc-platform-bss-ebs-csi-role</code></td>
      <td>EBS CSI driver role for Kubernetes persistent volumes.</td>
      <td>Yes</td>
      <td>AWS managed policy: <code>service-role/AmazonEBSCSIDriverPolicy</code></td>
      <td>Temporary placeholder trust policy is okay.</td>
      <td>
        Update trust to EKS OIDC provider for
        <code>system:serviceaccount:kube-system:ebs-csi-controller-sa</code>.
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>4</td>
      <td><code>dc-platform-bss-polaris-s3-role</code></td>
      <td>Polaris access to S3-backed Iceberg catalog and warehouse storage.</td>
      <td>Yes</td>
      <td>Custom S3 policy for bucket <code>dc-platform-bss-proto-lakehouse-7901580-us-east-1</code></td>
      <td>Temporary placeholder trust policy is okay.</td>
      <td>
        Update trust to EKS OIDC provider for
        <code>system:serviceaccount:polaris:polaris-sa</code>.
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>5</td>
      <td><code>dc-platform-bss-spark-s3-role</code></td>
      <td>Spark job access to S3-backed Iceberg data.</td>
      <td>Yes</td>
      <td>Custom S3 policy for bucket <code>dc-platform-bss-proto-lakehouse-7901580-us-east-1</code></td>
      <td>Temporary placeholder trust policy is okay.</td>
      <td>
        Update trust to EKS OIDC provider for
        <code>system:serviceaccount:spark:spark-sa</code>.
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>6</td>
      <td><code>dc-platform-bss-airflow-s3-role</code></td>
      <td>Airflow access to DAG assets, logs, and S3 data paths.</td>
      <td>Yes</td>
      <td>Custom S3 policy for bucket <code>dc-platform-bss-proto-lakehouse-7901580-us-east-1</code></td>
      <td>Temporary placeholder trust policy is okay.</td>
      <td>
        Update trust to EKS OIDC provider for
        <code>system:serviceaccount:airflow:airflow-sa</code>.
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>

  <h2>Custom S3 Policy Scope For Roles 4-6</h2>

  <table>
    <tr>
      <th>Resource</th>
      <th>Actions</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><code>arn:aws:s3:::dc-platform-bss-proto-lakehouse-7901580-us-east-1</code></td>
      <td>
        <code>s3:GetBucketLocation</code>,
        <code>s3:ListBucket</code>,
        <code>s3:ListBucketMultipartUploads</code>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><code>arn:aws:s3:::dc-platform-bss-proto-lakehouse-7901580-us-east-1/*</code></td>
      <td>
        <code>s3:GetObject</code>,
        <code>s3:PutObject</code>,
        <code>s3:DeleteObject</code>,
        <code>s3:AbortMultipartUpload</code>,
        <code>s3:ListMultipartUploadParts</code>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>

  <h2>OIDC Follow-Up After EKS Cluster Creation</h2>

  <p>
    After the EKS cluster is created, retrieve the OIDC issuer URL:
  </p>

  <p>
    <code>aws eks describe-cluster --region us-east-1 --name dc-platform-bss-eks-proto --query 'cluster.identity.oidc.issuer' --output text</code>
  </p>

  <p>
    Then update trust policies for roles 3-6 so each role allows
    <code>sts:AssumeRoleWithWebIdentity</code> from that EKS OIDC provider and only from the exact Kubernetes service account listed in the table above.
  </p>
</body>
</html>
